@@ -11,10 +11,14 @@ Process monitoring and configuration dashboard for [Hermes Agent](https://github
 - **Config** — View `config.yaml` and environment variables (read-only for safety)
 - **Cron** — View and manage scheduled agent jobs
 - **Skills** — Browse built-in and custom skills with full source inspection
+- **Personality** — View and edit agent personality and related runtime prompt content
+- **Files** — Browse and edit allowed runtime files within configured scopes
 - **Responsive** — Mobile-friendly layout with hamburger menu
 - **Dark/Light theme** — Toggle between themes
 - **Real-time updates** — WebSocket-based polling bridge, no agent code modification needed
 
+Edits you make in the WebUI (including on **Personality** and **Files**) are limited to **configured local roots** and **curated runtime files** exposed by the agent. The UI does not provide arbitrary filesystem access.
+
 ## Screenshots
 
 | Dashboard | Sessions |
@@ -182,6 +186,8 @@ Hermes WebUI reads from the agent's data files without modifying the agent's cor
 | **Config** | Read-only view of `config.yaml` sections and `.env` variables (sensitive values masked) |
 | **Cron** | List of scheduled cron jobs with status, schedule, and prompt preview |
 | **Skills** | Grid of built-in and custom skills with description, click to view full source |
+| **Personality** | Edit agent personality and related prompt/runtime text within allowed paths |
+| **Files** | Browse and edit runtime files under configured local roots; writes are scoped, not whole-disk |
 
